We study the QST under dissipative mechanisms in a way that is consistent with a circuit QED implementation based on a flux qubit coupled to an on-chip microwave cavity in the USC regime26, and including the effect of a finite temperature. The treatment that we use has also been applied to a recent implementation of the QRM at finite temperature30. Moreover, the leftmost and rightmost qubits could be implemented by means of transmon qubits52, 53 coupled to the edges of the microwave cavity. The dissipative dynamics is governed by the microscopic master equation in the Lindblad form ref. 54
